{{ template "global-ai-general-guidelines.md.tmpl" . -}}
- `AGENTS.md` is the canonical Codex rules file.

## Agent Dispatch

- Use Codex-native worker/sub-agent dispatch or an explicit dispatch recipe when available.
- Prefer project-specific or plugin-provided workers and skills over generic coordinator edits.
- Keep model and skill bindings explicit when dispatching work.
- When spawning search/exploration agents (`semble-search`, Explore, or similar), write prompts that describe what you
  need to know, not how to find it. State the question or goal; do not prescribe file paths, line numbers, or search
  commands. The agent has its own search strategy - over-specifying the approach overrides it and defeats the purpose of
  delegation.
- Keep the coordinating agent focused on context gathering, orchestration, verification, and user communication. Edit
  directly only when the task is trivial, no suitable Codex dispatch exists, or the required dispatch path is
  unavailable.

